
# **HR INTERNSHIP PROGRAM – OFFICIAL DOCUMENT**

## **Organization:** PearlThoughts

**Internship Role:** Human Resources Intern
**Duration:** 4 Weeks
**Mode:** Remote
**Working Days:** Monday to Friday
**Working Hours:** As assigned by HR Team

---

## **1. Internship Objective**

The objective of this HR Internship Program is to provide interns with **practical exposure to real-time HR operations**, including recruitment, candidate communication, internship handling, and screening techniques. This program is designed to help interns develop **professional HR skills** and understand **end-to-end people management processes** in an IT organization.

---

## **2. Scope of Internship**

During the internship period, interns will be involved in:

* Recruitment & sourcing activities
* Professional email communication
* Internship coordination & operations
* Resume screening & evaluation
* HR documentation and reporting

---

## **3. Internship Structure (Daily Task Plan)**

### **Week 1 – HR Basics & Hiring Platforms**

**Day 1**

* Company introduction & HR orientation
* Overview of recruitment lifecycle

**Day 2**

* Understanding job descriptions
* Drafting sample internship job descriptions

**Day 3**

* Introduction to hiring platforms
* LinkedIn sourcing overview

**Day 4**

* Internshala / Indeed platform overview
* Posting internship openings

**Day 5**

* Candidate sourcing
* Maintaining candidate database

---

### **Week 2 – Email Communication & Coordination**

**Day 6**

* Professional email etiquette
* Recruitment communication workflow

**Day 7**

* Drafting application acknowledgment & interview invite emails

**Day 8**

* Drafting selection, rejection, and on-hold emails

**Day 9**

* Sending emails to candidates
* Tracking responses and follow-ups

**Day 10**

* Interview scheduling
* Calendar management and reminders

---

### **Week 3 – Internship Handling & HR Operations**

**Day 11**

* Internship onboarding process
* Preparing onboarding checklist

**Day 12**

* Sharing joining instructions
* Adding interns to communication platforms

**Day 13**

* Attendance tracking system
* Creating attendance records

**Day 14**

* Task tracking & daily reporting
* Handling intern queries

**Day 15**

* Coordination with mentors and team leads
* Updating performance records

---

### **Week 4 – Screening & Performance Evaluation**

**Day 16**

* Resume screening techniques
* Shortlisting criteria

**Day 17**

* Screening resumes & preparing shortlist

**Day 18**

* Telephonic screening basics
* Mock screening calls

**Day 19**

* Performance evaluation methods
* Preparing feedback reports

**Day 20**

* Final internship report submission
* Feedback discussion and internship closure

---

## **4. Tools & Platforms Used**

* Hiring Platforms: LinkedIn, Internshala, Indeed
* Communication: Email, Microsoft Teams / Discord
* Documentation & Tracking: Google Sheets, Google Drive
* Scheduling: Google Calendar

---

## **5. Performance Evaluation Criteria**

Interns will be evaluated based on:

* Task completion & accuracy
* Professional communication skills
* Consistency & punctuality
* Learning attitude & initiative
* Team coordination

---

## **6. Internship Completion & Certification**

* Interns who successfully complete the internship and meet performance expectations will receive an **Internship Completion Certificate**.
* Based on performance, interns may be considered for:

  * Extended internship
  * Paid internship opportunity
  * Full-time employment (subject to availability)

---

## **7. Code of Conduct**

* Maintain professional communication at all times
* Follow company policies and timelines
* Ensure confidentiality of company and candidate data
* Respect team members and organizational hierarchy

---

## **8. Declaration**

This internship program is intended solely for learning and skill development. Completion of the internship does not guarantee employment unless explicitly communicated by the organization.

